Chancellor Angela Merkel called for calm Monday in an escalating dispute with Turkey, a day after President Recep Tayyip Erdogan labelled a German ban on rallies by his ministers &#8220;Nazi practices&#8221;.&#8220;To our Turkish partners, let us talk openly and critically, but let us remember the special meaning of our close relationship and let cool heads prevail,&#8221; said Merkel&#8217;s spokesman Steffen Seibert.-AFP